==English==

===Etymology===
Originally from postwar French (1952), ''néonazi'', used to describe any number of movements, which saw themselves as believers of [[Nazi]] ideology or whose ideology had similar attributes. The term spread throughout the Western world aquiring a broader usage.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Person who believes in a version of Nazi ideology.
# Person who believes in a white supremecist ideology especially one who uses Nazi iconography.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Describing a group made up of Neo-Nazis.
# Describing a group which believes in such an ideology.